<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: This ring looks awesome, why do I never/almost never see it?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: It is extremely tedious, and a lot of it is hit-or-miss luck. The first ring you have to collect two of the very rare HQ Tundra Kodiak Pelts, which can take anywhere from 30 minutes to months. Finding Rodrick and the invasion plans are a tedious wait as well. The dwarf for the second quest is simply annoying and gets in more trouble than Kragstomper. Depending on server dynamics, people may be in competition for Garadain Glacierbane to do the 8th quest. The 9th quest requires some tedious camps, as well as a high level brewer (of which there are few). The 10th ring is not doable by a run-of-the-mill guild either.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: This sounds altogether too much like the Ragefire camp.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
